##STREAMS
  --Stream is essentially a change data capture (CDC) mechanism. It records row-level changes (DML operations) made to a source table since the last time the stream was consumed.
  --Change Tracking: When enabled, Snowflake maintains hidden metadata about row changes. This metadata is what streams query to return only the "delta" (new/changed/deleted rows).
  --If CHANGE_TRACKING is not set to TRUE, you can still query the table normally, but streams won’t be able to capture incremental changes.
  --Create streams for all the raw tables
    ALTER TABLE DBTPROJECT.RAW.FACT_ORDERS SET CHANGE_TRACKING = TRUE;
    ALTER TABLE DBTPROJECT.RAW.DIM_CUSTOMERS SET CHANGE_TRACKING = TRUE;
    ALTER TABLE DBTPROJECT.RAW.DIM_PRODUCTS SET CHANGE_TRACKING = TRUE;
    ALTER TABLE DBTPROJECT.RAW.DIM_STORES SET CHANGE_TRACKING = TRUE;
    ALTER TABLE DBTPROJECT.RAW.DIM_DATES SET CHANGE_TRACKING = TRUE;

